##Day and night on the sixth floor of the critical care area in Wuhan

MICRO-SIGNAL ESQUIRECN

Function description, fashion makes sir, Sir defines fashion.

Wuhan new crown pneumonia is the most intense, a medical team from Nanjing into Wuhan Tongji Hospital, began a difficult battle. Meanwhile, our editor Chen Weixi walked into the ICU with a video camera, recording the doctors and patients working side by side day and night.

Starting from today (March 9) , Mr. Fashion will join tencent news to release a series of short documentary film "Six floors of Wuhan Critical Care Area" . Please stay tuned. This is a pilot photo story.

Photographer: Chen Weixi

Photo credit: Xin Yuan

Editor: Du Qiang

ESQUIRE and tencent news

Exclusive cooperation content, declined to reprint

At 1 a.m. on Feb. 11, the door handle of the entrance to the ward of Wuhan Tongji Hospital in Guanggu district shook uneasily.

Outside, 44 patients with newly diagnosed pneumonia were anxiously waiting to check in; inside, the medical team that took over the sixth floor of the E1 wing of the Guanggu Hospital district was making final preparations for admission to the Split Second. The door opens, the patients rush in, and the first group of patients arrive. Only 30 hours had passed since they landed in Wuhan.

The team, which took over the sixth floor of the E1 district of the Tongji Guanggu Hospital district in Wuhan, was made up of medical staff from the Drum Tower Hospital in Nanjing, as well as hospitals in Luhe and Gaochun District. After the installation of ECG monitoring, breathing machine and other preparatory work is ready, the medical staff than OK gesture, ready to start receiving patients. There are 17 wards in Guanggu Hospital district, managed by 17 medical teams from Shanghai, Shandong, Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Guangdong and Fujian provinces, with a total of 850 beds. Each ward has 50 beds and 130 medical staff, including 30 doctors and 100 nurses.

As soon as the door opened, patients rushed in. In order to ensure the safe and orderly admission of patients, medical staff one by one to inquire about the patient's physical condition, and arrange beds, but also to constantly calm the patient's mood, maintain on-site order. That night, after a fierce battle, all 44 patients diagnosed with NCP were admitted to the hospital within 3 hours.

The medical staff came to the ward to observe and record the patient's condition.

Once the patient is in place, health care workers begin to think and discuss treatment options.

In the early morning of February 22, a critically ill patient was temporarily transferred to the ward. The medical staff rotated around the patient 24 hours a day, 6 shifts a day. The next morning, a nurse on the morning shift wrote "come on" on a medical glove and placed it under the patient's endotracheal tube to prevent it from bending and sagging.

Every morning at 10:00 a.m. , a panel of Experts Discusses Treatment Options. As of 24 February, a total of 59 patients had been admitted and 10 had been discharged.

In addition to paying real-time attention to the physical condition of the seriously ill patients, the medical staff should pay special attention to the psychological fluctuation of the patients due to the change of their condition. Anxiety, restlessness, fear, irritability, depression... These are the common emotions of patients with severe illness. Behind every emotion is a poignant story. The new Crown Epidemic statistics are updated in real time, and behind the abstract numbers are countless living individual narratives.

Wang, who is in her 70s, is not very ill, but she is very anxious. One day, she even ran out of the ward and shouted to the doctor, "I'm dying. I want to go home. ". A medical team liaison is also a psychologist who is responsible for medical management and liaison, while at the same time playing the role of professional psychological counseling for patients.

In the course of talking to grandma Wang, I learned that she had not been able to get in touch with her family because she was rushed to the hospital without her mobile phone. The liaison got a pen and paper and wrote down the telephone number of the old man's son. Later, the nurse dialed the telephone, the son let Wang Grandma rest in peace.

The nurse said that the old man should be worried about his son, so after hearing the news of his son, to make sure that his son is okay, she was also relieved. On February 26, Wang was released from the hospital after a successful recovery.

An elderly couple who fell ill at the same time was admitted to the hospital, but because there were only three beds in each ward, the two elderly patients could not be assigned to the same room, but were assigned to the adjacent ward. Grandma is in a mild condition, but GRANDPA is in a serious condition. In order not to let grandma worry, Grandpa always refused to answer her phone. The medical staff who learned the situation took the initiative to act as a relay station for communication between the two elderly people. They went to see their grandfather first every day and told him, "grandma cares about you very much and is waiting to leave with you. " Then pass on some of GRANDPA's information to grandma as appropriate.

Late One night, GRANDPA's condition has changed, grandma unexpectedly keen to feel. A nurse said of the old couple, "at a time like this, the word 'love' is magnified. ". At present GRANDPA has passed the most dangerous period, the condition tends to be stable.

A nearly 80-year-old elderly patient ran out of the ward, the medical staff to calm, will be persuaded back to the room. The medical staff couldn't understand him very well, at first they thought he just wanted to go home, but later, after observation, they determined that the old man might have Alzheimer's Disease and Alcoholic Encephalopathy, and that he was suffering from a disturbance of consciousness, and the doctor gave him appropriate medication, nurses also do their best to provide care.

According to the requirements, patients can not visit each other or in the corridor to move around, but the elderly always take the opportunity to run into the corridor, mouth muttering, always like looking for something. The nurse once asked him if he was looking for a home and a bed, and he said, "yes. " He helped him to the bedside, but soon he came out again.

Zhou Ayi (first right) the first day of admission, dragging the body in the room to constantly wipe. The head nurse persuaded him to return to bed.

In the hospital bed, Aunt Zhou spoke of her own experience crying, tears soaked mask. She and her parents were infected, and her husband and child were quarantined. The 77 year old mother of Parkinson, who had been paralyzed for years, had died at home, and the 81 year old father had been admitted to another ward in the same hospital, unable to reach him because he could not use a mobile phone. Zhou was worried about her father's health after he was diagnosed with diabetes and had a artificial pacemaker installed. The head nurse explained that in the psychology of disease, her repeated cleaning of the room was a kind of escape mechanism, a mechanical repetition of the behavior to escape psychological trauma. Subsequently, with the help of the head nurse, Aunt Zhou finally contacted her father and was able to sleep peacefully.

The patient repeatedly showed the tongue coating to others, he felt his tongue coating is strange, may be a sign of deterioration of the condition, very anxious. Medical staff explained to the patient that it was an oral ulcer, gave him medication, and adjusted his diet to semi-fluid. Special Period, the subtle change on the body, can cause the psychological fluctuation of the patient.

Behind the newly admitted patient is a piece of paper that says, "confirmed patient, please step away. ". The note was written by the patient's granddaughter as a friendly reminder to stay away from infections. When the outbreak came, people kept a safe distance from each other, but it also inspired kindness among strangers. When the patient was taken care of, the note was removed.

The TV in the ward was tuned to the variety channel in an effort to keep patients away from news about the outbreak. In the treatment phase, news related to the epidemic is "isolated" , maintaining a relatively stable mood, is particularly important for the recovery of patients.

We don't talk to many of the patients in the ward, and most of the time we just watch TV together.

Although the same patient, but due to the severity of the disease, but also worry about cross-infection may aggravate the disease. That's why patients in the next bed close their curtains when they talk.

A patient stood in front of a French window and looked out.

Early recovery and discharge from hospital is not only the greatest wish of patients, but also the most urgent wish of medical staff. As the paramedic said to the patient, "please work with US until the outbreak is over, we want to go home, we want to take off our masks and breathe. ". "But in the epidemic has not yet ended, the medical staff still must devote day after day to the treatment, the nursing work.

Tongji Hospital Guanggu Hospital area, is mainly to treat serious patients in the hospital area, while undertaking the urgent task of heavy treatment, medical staff in self-protection is also no negligence. Before entering the ward, put on a mask, buckle on goggles, wear protective clothing and write your name on it, becoming the most ritualistic thing of the day. In addition to their names, they often improvise graffiti, or homesick for home-cooked meals, or for loved ones who are far away, or for those who rejoice in their desire... in wards filled with the smell of illness, panic and death, the lightness and optimism of these brush strokes is especially valuable when the breathing inside the suit becomes burdensome.

"Week Black Duck" , "salt water duck" , they are the specialties of Wuhan and Nanjing respectively, here they have another meaning: One City to another city rushed to the rescue, watch and help.

Xing Ling, a nurse, wrote the names of her two daughters on her chest and said, "mommy loves you. ". Since the outbreak, the daughter has been in the grandparents home, Xingling from the third day of the Lunar New Year has not seen them. She said that her eldest daughter was four and a half years old. She knew in a daze that her mother had gone to Wuhan to "fight viruses and monsters. " Her second daughter was two and a half years old. She didn't know what her mother was going to do, but she still missed her mother very much.

On Valentine's Day, nurse Zhou Yun's protective clothing said, "Happy Valentine's Day. " "Love, Wuhan. " . Zhou Yun says she had a hero's dream when she was a child, always braiding her hair and pretending to be Mulan. Now chi-aid Wuhan, the first-line anti-epidemic has been her hero dream.

Although members of the medical team make use of the medical supplies available before they start work each day, they enter and leave the "red zone" every day to deal with the invisible virus. They are in a highly contaminated environment, are still the ones closest to danger. On March 6, Ding Xiangyang, a member of the central guidance team and deputy secretary-general of the State Council, said that more than 3,000 health care workers in Hubei Province had contracted the new pneumonia, and that more than 40,000 health care workers in Hubei Province had not been reported to have contracted it.

At high risk of infection, health care workers carefully disinfect the eyes with alcohol swabs at the end of the day. The fear of infection goes hand in hand, and the possibility of infection can only be minimized with the best possible protection and careful disinfection.

At the end of the day, the nurse wipes her ear with an alcohol swab to disinfect it.

Marks left by masks and protective clothing on the faces of medical staff. In addition, wearing protective clothing can not easily drink water, toilet, but also medical staff to overcome the difficulties. Breathless protective clothing is worn for hours at a time, often sweaty at the end of the day.

At six o'clock in the morning, the medical team took a bus from the hotel to the hospital 10 kilometers away. They were very close colleagues, but they didn't talk much in the bus. Soon, they will begin a new day of intensive rescue work.

The medical team took a bus to the hospital. The trees on the street outside the bus window had beautiful shadows, and the branches were beginning to show their spring.

Spring is here, but according to a Feb. 21 meeting of the Politburo of the Communist Party of China, the national inflection point has not yet arrived. Wang Chen, vice president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and a specialist in respiratory and critical care medicine, also told News 1 + 1 that the new pneumonia could turn into a chronic disease that co exists with humans like the flu. There is still a long way to go, but at least tens of millions of front-line health care workers are still on the way.
